Cluster Architecture:
=====================

- K8s Architecture
- ETCD for beginners
- ETCD in K8s
- Kube API Server
- Control Managers
- Kube Scheduler
- Kubelet
- Kube Proxy


- Cluster info is stored in ETCD (K:V)
- Scheduler identifies the right container to place on the workers nodes
- Controllers take care of the overall health of the Cluster

    - Node Controller
    - Replication Controller


- Kube API is the primary communication components of the K8s Cluster
- Kubelet is an agent that runs on each nodes of the Cluster
- Kube-proxy takes care of the internal communication in the worker nodes


Find all components in  /etc/kubernetes/manifests folder
